    &intro;


      User Manual

        Introduction



          The User Manual introduces the Aranea API used by application programmers omitting the framework inner workings. This part talks about widgets, custom jsp tag library used to render them, a data binding component and a database-backed listing component. One can both read this part through as a book, or find the necessary information using searching or lookup. This part is a must-read for any serious user of Aranea framework.


      &widgets;
      &jsp;    
      &forms;
      &lists;


      System Manual

        Introduction



          The System Manual describes the core framework API, framework configuration and framework extension. It goes in depth describing the core framework interaction and may be not necessary for a novice user. This part is intended for system programmers, architects and other users that have to deal with debugging, extending or configuring the framework.


